1
00:00:49,983 --> 00:00:51,850
Am I ready?

2
00:00:54,587 --> 00:00:57,156
You belong here.

3
00:02:30,383 --> 00:02:33,085
Morning, Mrs. Kimbale.
Morning!

4
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:42,461
Brian, still sleeping.

5
00:02:42,463 --> 00:02:43,362
Phiona.

6
00:02:43,364 --> 00:02:47,366
Richard!
My little brother, get up!

7
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:54,882
Go away

8
00:02:54,967 --> 00:02:56,007
You go away

9
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:24,002
It's only one.
It's 500 each.

10
00:03:24,004 --> 00:03:25,637
All five?

11
00:03:27,707 --> 00:03:29,041
- All five?
- Yeah.

12
00:03:29,043 --> 00:03:30,142
2,500.

13
00:03:30,144 --> 00:03:31,777
Hey, when you want bargain?

14
00:03:31,779 --> 00:03:33,512
Sir, pay me 1,000.

15
00:03:35,516 --> 00:03:38,250
Two bags! Two bags!
Two bags, please.

16
00:03:38,252 --> 00:03:40,219
Your mother
still owes me some money.

17
00:03:40,221 --> 00:03:42,187
We'll make it up tomorrow.

18
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:47,559
That's it.
Now, tell your mother

19
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:49,361
I need my money.

20
00:04:07,113 --> 00:04:08,547
Oh, my god, Phiona.

21
00:04:08,549 --> 00:04:11,450
He rode me on his boda.

22
00:04:11,452 --> 00:04:13,952
Latest model, Chinese roadster.

23
00:04:13,954 --> 00:04:15,053
China! Yeah!

24
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:16,755
Ask your sister why this man

25
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:18,190
takes young girls
on his boda boda.

26
00:04:18,192 --> 00:04:22,127
Mother asks, "why does he take
young girls on his boda?"

27
00:04:22,129 --> 00:04:24,563
Theo has a big heart!

28
00:04:24,864 --> 00:04:25,130
Brian.

29
00:04:25,132 --> 00:04:28,634
I think she should keep this
boy at a proper distance.

30
00:04:28,636 --> 00:04:30,602
You must get 1,000, Phiona.

31
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:33,505
No, mama, it's too much.
I'm tired!

32
00:04:33,507 --> 00:04:33,872
So am I.

33
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:36,775
Patricia's mother does not
force her to sell. I'm tired.

34
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:40,279
Patricia's mother has
a husband who is alive.

35
00:04:40,281 --> 00:04:43,615
Did your father leave me
any money when he died?

36
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,285
Theo!

37
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,370
Night, let's go

38
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:50,689
Night, where you going?

39
00:04:50,691 --> 00:04:52,090
To get a ride.

40
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:55,560
Ah...

41
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:57,929
Are you the mother
or the sister?

42
00:04:57,931 --> 00:05:00,098
For you I'm not either.

43
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:03,869
And I know a hyena
when I see it.

44
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:10,375
You keep away from my daughter.

45
00:05:10,377 --> 00:05:11,043
Stop it, mummy!

46
00:05:11,045 --> 00:05:14,479
If I see you sniffing
around here again...

47
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,848
I will burn this
pile of tin to scrap!

48
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:17,349
You be careful.

49
00:05:17,351 --> 00:05:20,519
This bike is worth more
than everything you have.

50
00:05:23,756 --> 00:05:24,823
Theo.

51
00:05:24,825 --> 00:05:26,124
Me, I'm gone.

52
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:27,492
Theo!

53
00:05:28,261 --> 00:05:30,062
I will never forgive you
for this.

54
00:05:30,064 --> 00:05:31,496
I don't need your forgiveness!

55
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:35,834
I need you to sell maize
to feed your brothers!

56
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:37,636
Go.

57
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:39,104
Go!

58
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:44,843
Shirts. Shirts.
Shirts is outside.

59
00:05:46,979 --> 00:05:48,447
Shirts is out.

60
00:05:48,881 --> 00:05:51,483
Come here.
Shirts is outside you.

61
00:05:51,485 --> 00:05:52,951
Spread out! Spread out!

62
00:05:52,953 --> 00:05:57,022
Joseph! Long passes!
Keep playing, keep playing.

63
00:05:58,925 --> 00:06:00,158
Katende.

64
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,362
They turned you down.

65
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:05,197
I warned you.

66
00:06:05,199 --> 00:06:07,499
They don't care
about your marks.

67
00:06:07,501 --> 00:06:09,801
Only your family status.

68
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:12,838
I surrender, my friend.

69
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:16,007
I will accept the position
at your ministry...

70
00:06:16,009 --> 00:06:17,809
But only until I'm able to find

71
00:06:17,811 --> 00:06:18,477
an engineering job.

72
00:06:18,479 --> 00:06:22,381
What makes you think
I still have a job for you?

73
00:06:27,653 --> 00:06:30,322
So, you would be willing
to restore hope...

74
00:06:30,324 --> 00:06:34,493
And transform the lives
of children through sports.

75
00:06:34,495 --> 00:06:36,495
Full time.

76
00:06:36,596 --> 00:06:37,229
I would.

77
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:40,031
<i>Welcome.
Katwe needs you.</i>

78
00:06:52,011 --> 00:06:53,845
One<i> maca?</i>
Just 300.

79
00:07:00,119 --> 00:07:04,589
I said, no, thank you. Gosh!

80
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:07,759
Thank you. Keep dancing.
Keep dancing.

81
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:09,261
Thank you, madam.

82
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:15,100
Take my bucket, Phiona.

83
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:16,701
Where do you go every day?

84
00:07:16,703 --> 00:07:17,335
Ah!

85
00:07:17,337 --> 00:07:22,073
Brian! We haven't made
1,000 shillings yet!

86
00:07:27,780 --> 00:07:28,980
Mmm-hmm.

87
00:07:28,982 --> 00:07:30,782
Let's go!

88
00:07:32,351 --> 00:07:34,119
Go! Go! Go! Go!

89
00:07:36,189 --> 00:07:37,856
Why aren't you taking part?

90
00:07:37,858 --> 00:07:41,426
You can break bones
playing football.

91
00:07:41,428 --> 00:07:43,261
My mother refuses.

92
00:07:43,263 --> 00:07:45,030
No money for doctors.

93
00:07:45,032 --> 00:07:48,767
Me, I have broken a few bones
playing football myself.

94
00:07:48,769 --> 00:07:51,169
Joseph, what did I just say?

95
00:07:51,171 --> 00:07:54,072
There's another game
you can play.

96
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:56,541
Have you heard of chess?

97
00:07:56,543 --> 00:07:57,175
Me, I know.

98
00:07:57,177 --> 00:08:00,111
You kiss a person
and try to catch them.

99
00:08:01,949 --> 00:08:04,883
No. It is a board game.

100
00:08:04,885 --> 00:08:06,418
I can teach you.

101
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:08,119
I don't want.

102
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:10,255
Too bad, eh?

103
00:08:10,257 --> 00:08:13,191
I thought you might like
beating city boys.

104
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:14,659
What do you mean?

105
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:16,995
When I was at school...

106
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:19,464
<i>the city boys
with their gold watches,</i>

107
00:08:19,466 --> 00:08:20,298
<i>they loved this game.</i>

108
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:23,201
<i>They had contests
to see who was the best.</i>

109
00:08:23,203 --> 00:08:25,103
I'm ready when you're ready.

110
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,673
Me, I was an orphan.

111
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:31,843
<i>So, like you,
I had no gold watch...</i>

112
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:34,980
<i>But I practiced my chess.</i>

113
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,820
And I defeated them all.

114
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:50,161
Thank you.
I have tuition to pay.

115
00:08:54,901 --> 00:08:56,668
Bring us this game.

116
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:58,336
You want to play chess?

117
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,873
Good.

118
00:09:23,529 --> 00:09:24,829
Morning.
Morning, Brian.

119
00:09:24,831 --> 00:09:26,131
- Morning.
- Morning, Brian.

120
00:09:26,133 --> 00:09:27,365
Morning.
Morning, guys!

121
00:09:27,367 --> 00:09:28,833
Hi, Gloria.
Morning.

122
00:09:28,835 --> 00:09:30,835
- Joseph, hi.
- Morning, Ivan.

123
00:09:30,837 --> 00:09:33,071
Hey, here comes coach.

124
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,407
Good morning, pioneers!

125
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:37,709
Good morning, coach!

126
00:10:16,248 --> 00:10:18,283
Where are the cups?

127
00:10:32,198 --> 00:10:33,965
Come for porridge!

128
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:42,140
Young girl.

129
00:10:43,009 --> 00:10:44,242
Come.

130
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,911
Come inside. Come.

131
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,784
Are you hungry?

132
00:10:55,921 --> 00:10:56,955
Ugh!

133
00:10:56,957 --> 00:10:57,789
You smell!

134
00:10:57,791 --> 00:10:59,324
Who is that girl?

135
00:10:59,592 --> 00:11:02,093
Have you been running
in mud like a pig?

136
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:03,428
Go away, smelly girl.

137
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:05,430
This is not your game.

138
00:11:13,372 --> 00:11:15,840
Let go!

139
00:11:15,975 --> 00:11:18,810
Let go! Let go!

140
00:11:20,813 --> 00:11:22,947
Next time
I will tear that fat nose

141
00:11:22,949 --> 00:11:24,082
right off your head!

142
00:11:24,084 --> 00:11:26,851
Who else is brave?

143
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,188
Me, I'm not brave.

144
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:33,191
Hey! A fighter.

145
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:35,860
What is your name?
Phiona.

146
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:36,828
Welcome.

147
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,364
This is a place for fighters.

148
00:12:05,357 --> 00:12:07,225
Phiona.

149
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,576
I will take these rotten ones
from yesterday...

150
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:27,145
But you should be
giving them to me for free.

151
00:12:27,147 --> 00:12:28,713
I'll give you something for free

152
00:12:28,715 --> 00:12:30,782
when you give me
something for free.

153
00:12:30,784 --> 00:12:32,050
Here.

154
00:12:32,551 --> 00:12:33,618
No charge.

155
00:12:46,165 --> 00:12:49,934
Abdul, go and play ruwenda.

156
00:12:49,936 --> 00:12:52,670
Gloria, would you
please show Phiona

157
00:12:52,672 --> 00:12:54,539
how to move the pieces.

158
00:12:55,307 --> 00:12:55,907
Mmm...

159
00:12:55,909 --> 00:12:58,843
We must be merciful
to the wicked.

160
00:12:58,845 --> 00:13:00,078
Hmm?

161
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:06,918
This is little man.

162
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,119
His boda is broken,

163
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:10,288
so he can only bump into things.

164
00:13:10,489 --> 00:13:13,424
Beep, beep, beep.

165
00:13:13,426 --> 00:13:15,493
This is the queen.

166
00:13:15,495 --> 00:13:18,897
She is the most powerful
of all the pieces.

167
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:20,932
What do they all do?

168
00:13:20,934 --> 00:13:22,734
They kill each other.

169
00:13:22,736 --> 00:13:25,069
See, dead.

170
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:28,640
This is the president.

171
00:13:30,342 --> 00:13:34,279
If your president is trapped,
nowhere to go...

172
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:36,648
You say, checkmate.

173
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:37,315
Checkmate.

174
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:41,119
Now, go away.
I don't like your bad smell.

175
00:14:04,643 --> 00:14:07,312
Hey, Phiona!
How is your life?

176
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:08,813
It is fine.

177
00:14:57,272 --> 00:14:58,652
Let us pray

178
00:14:58,653 --> 00:15:01,466
Oh, lord, bless the food
we are going to eat. Amen.

179
00:15:01,468 --> 00:15:02,767
Amen.

180
00:15:03,535 --> 00:15:05,503
Mom, I'm satisfied.

181
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:07,572
You have my share, mom.

182
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:10,008
I'm satisfied, mom.

183
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:11,943
You have eaten.

184
00:15:11,945 --> 00:15:13,578
How?

185
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:14,913
Hmm...

186
00:15:14,915 --> 00:15:18,583
You better not be
eating the maize.

187
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:27,510
Look, the fire glows

188
00:15:29,628 --> 00:15:33,631
Yes! Yes, I beat you.

189
00:15:33,633 --> 00:15:36,768
Aha! The pig has had a bath.

190
00:15:37,136 --> 00:15:39,570
Joseph,
you're playing with fire.

191
00:15:39,572 --> 00:15:40,939
Quiet, Benjamin.

192
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:42,040
Coach.

193
00:15:42,042 --> 00:15:45,743
Coach calls it promoting.

194
00:15:45,745 --> 00:15:48,112
But I call it queening.

195
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:51,749
When you scoot little man
down the board...

196
00:15:51,751 --> 00:15:54,185
Square by square...

197
00:15:54,187 --> 00:15:56,621
When he reaches the back rank...

198
00:15:58,190 --> 00:16:00,091
He becomes...

199
00:16:02,227 --> 00:16:03,194
Mmm?

200
00:16:03,196 --> 00:16:05,129
A queen.

201
00:16:07,232 --> 00:16:08,132
In chess...

202
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:12,570
The small one
can become the big one.

203
00:16:12,572 --> 00:16:15,139
That's why I like it.

204
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:16,941
Hmm.

205
00:16:22,748 --> 00:16:25,416
You take care of Richard.

206
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:27,952
I'm going to find night.

207
00:16:51,810 --> 00:16:53,344
Phiona!

208
00:16:53,979 --> 00:16:56,047
Phiona!
Mmm?

209
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:00,785
Night.
Come.

210
00:17:01,954 --> 00:17:03,154
Night?

211
00:17:03,156 --> 00:17:06,357
Mother just went
to look for you.

212
00:17:06,959 --> 00:17:07,992
Here.

213
00:17:07,994 --> 00:17:09,527
Where did you get this?

214
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:11,729
I told you.
Theo is kind hearted.

215
00:17:11,731 --> 00:17:15,666
You are not staying with him,
are you, night?

216
00:17:15,668 --> 00:17:19,871
Mother stayed with a man.
In a few years, so shall you.

217
00:17:19,873 --> 00:17:22,740
No, no, no. Not me.

218
00:17:24,777 --> 00:17:26,110
Night...

219
00:17:26,112 --> 00:17:29,680
Do you think god wants
bad fortune for us?

220
00:17:29,682 --> 00:17:31,349
Why would you say this?

221
00:17:31,351 --> 00:17:34,886
Because since papa and Juliet
passed away...

222
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:37,422
It seems he is angry with us.

223
00:17:37,424 --> 00:17:39,624
I don't think
god cares about us,

224
00:17:39,626 --> 00:17:41,559
one way or the other.

225
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:50,334
Bye, my sister.

226
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:04,082
Ivan, when you fetch water
for your mother...

227
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:06,317
Do you just go
any time of the day?

228
00:18:06,319 --> 00:18:08,086
Or do you think a bit first?

229
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:09,954
I think a bit.
About what?

230
00:18:09,956 --> 00:18:12,957
There are long lines
for water in the morning,

231
00:18:12,959 --> 00:18:14,625
so I plan when I will go.

232
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:15,693
Ah! A plan.

233
00:18:15,695 --> 00:18:17,662
And I cannot arrive
too late because

234
00:18:17,664 --> 00:18:19,864
I could get robbed
on the way home.

235
00:18:19,866 --> 00:18:20,765
So, on my way,

236
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,533
I cut through the valley
to save time.

237
00:18:22,535 --> 00:18:24,102
And what happens
when the rain comes?

238
00:18:24,104 --> 00:18:25,603
The waters come down the hill.

239
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:26,904
And do you get washed away?

240
00:18:26,906 --> 00:18:28,706
No, I climb in my hammock.

241
00:18:28,708 --> 00:18:31,275
Your hammock! Good plan.

242
00:18:31,277 --> 00:18:34,612
Threats from many directions.

243
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,014
Robbers.

244
00:18:37,516 --> 00:18:39,283
Angry property owners.

245
00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:41,319
Floods.

246
00:18:41,753 --> 00:18:43,788
And other dangers.

247
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:48,926
How can this bishop survive?

248
00:18:53,165 --> 00:18:55,633
Coach, no way.

249
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:57,535
Eh, eh, eh. Look.

250
00:18:57,669 --> 00:18:59,937
Look at it closely.

251
00:19:04,076 --> 00:19:05,109
F-3?

252
00:19:05,111 --> 00:19:07,612
Yes, f-3.

253
00:19:07,679 --> 00:19:09,013
He is safe there.

254
00:19:09,015 --> 00:19:11,482
Yes. In today's game...

255
00:19:11,717 --> 00:19:15,119
Bishop is safe on f-3.

256
00:19:15,121 --> 00:19:16,988
When you first looked
at this position...

257
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:20,958
Perhaps you thought there was
no safe haven for bishop.

258
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,126
But, you looked closely.

259
00:19:22,128 --> 00:19:25,763
You analyzed the threats.
You made a plan.

260
00:19:25,765 --> 00:19:27,965
And bishop found safety, eh?

261
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:29,834
Use your minds.

262
00:19:30,402 --> 00:19:31,169
Follow your plans.

263
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:34,539
And you will all find
safe squares.

264
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:39,277
Me, teacher!
Me, teacher! Me, teacher!

265
00:19:39,279 --> 00:19:40,845
Nearly two million years ago...

266
00:19:40,847 --> 00:19:45,516
East Africans were the first
to master the use of fire.

267
00:19:45,518 --> 00:19:50,321
So, were we the first
to eat kikomando?

268
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:55,826
Hey.
Hey.

269
00:19:55,828 --> 00:19:58,563
The beautiful
Mrs. Katende.

270
00:19:58,565 --> 00:20:00,331
Hello.

271
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:04,735
Some days ago, this girl, Phiona,
came for the first time.

272
00:20:04,737 --> 00:20:06,771
She was not clean.

273
00:20:06,773 --> 00:20:09,974
Ivan and the boys
teased her very badly.

274
00:20:09,976 --> 00:20:12,677
Ivan is not
